  <section id="faq" class="py-16 md:py-20 fade-in-section" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
      <div style="border: 1.5px solid var(--color-warm-black); border-radius: var(--radius-card); padding: 40px;">
        <p class="type-overline text-stone mb-4">FAQ</p>
        <h2 id="faq-heading" class="type-h2 text-warm-black mb-10">Common questions.</h2>

        <div class="divide-y divide-warm-black/10">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>Do I need to know how to code?</span>
              <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p class="type-body text-warm-mid pb-2">No. Describe what you need in plain language. AI agents handle the architecture, frontend, backend, and database. When things get complex, real developers step&nbsp;in.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>What if I already started building on another platform?</span>
              <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p class="type-body text-warm-mid pb-2">Bring it. We can work with what you've started or help you start fresh &mdash; whichever gets you to launch&nbsp;faster.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>Do I own the code?</span>
              <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p class="type-body text-warm-mid pb-2">Completely. Clean, documented code that's yours. Hand it to any developer. Move it anywhere. No&nbsp;lock-in.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              <span>Why not just use Cursor, ChatGPT, or Claude Code?</span>
              <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p class="type-body text-warm-mid pb-2">Those tools are powerful &mdash; for developers. They require you to debug errors, make architecture decisions, and handle deployment. AgentQ is for people who want to describe what they need and get working software&nbsp;back.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

